item.description:
Description Create trigger: link pipeline to trigger-event.
Command codefresh create trigger &lt;event-uri&gt; &lt;pipeline&gt;
Aliases codefresh create t &lt;event-uri&gt; &lt;pipeline&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     event-uri   trigger-event URI   pipeline   pipeline to be triggered by the trigger-event    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information   - -filter   trigger filter name=condition pairs    Examples Create trigger by linking 5a43&hellip; pipeline to the DockerHub codefresh/fortune push event codefresh create trigger registry:dockerhub:codefresh:fortune:push 5a439664af73ad0001f3ece0

the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higher Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation through NPM registry.
Install: npm install -g codefresh
Install a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: npm install -g codefresh
Update to a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@${VERSION}

Description Create a config context.
Command codefresh create context config &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information   - -variable -v  Variables list    Examples Create a config. codefresh create context config my-config -v key1=valu1 -v key2=value2

the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higher Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation using YARN.
Install: yarn global add codefresh
Install a specific version: yarn global add codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: yarn global upgrade codefresh
Update to a specific version: yarn global upgrade codefresh@{VERSION}

Description Create a composition.
Command codefresh create composition &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh create com &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of composition    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information   - -variable -v  Variables list   - -advanced   Advanced composition   - -compose-file -c  Path to docker-compose.

Description Delete trigger: unlink pipeline from trigger-event.
Command codefresh delete trigger &lt;event-uri&gt; &lt;pipeline&gt;
Aliases codefresh delete t &lt;event-uri&gt; &lt;pipeline&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     event-uri   trigger-event URI (as defined by trigger type[/kind]). required   pipeline   pipeline ID. required    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information    Examples Delete trigger by unlinking 5a43&hellip; pipeline from the DockerHub codefresh/fortune push event codefresh delete trigger registry:dockerhub:codefresh:fortune:push 5a439664af73ad0001f3ece0

Description Create a secret context.
Command codefresh create context secret &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Name of context    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information   - -variable -v  Variables list    Examples Create a secret. codefresh create context secret my-secret -v key1=valu1 -v key2=value2

Description Show logs of a build.
Command codefresh logs &lt;id&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     id   Build id    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information   - -f   Continue showing build logs until it will finish    Examples Get logs of build ID codefresh logs ID

You can run the CLI using our official docker image which is published to Dockerhub
Pull the latest version: docker pull codefresh/cli
Pull a specific version: docker pull codefresh/cli:${VERSION}

Description Delete a composition.
Command codefresh delete composition &lt;name&gt;
Aliases codefresh delete com &lt;name&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     name   Composition name    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information    Examples Delete a composition codefresh delete composition NAME

Description Delete an environment.
Command codefresh delete environment &lt;id&gt;
Aliases codefresh delete env &lt;id&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     id   Environment id    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information    Examples Delete environment ID codefresh delete environment ID

Description Delete trigger-event.
Command codefresh delete trigger-event &lt;event-uri&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     event-uri   trigger-event URI    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information   - -context   context with credentials required to setup event on remote system    Examples Delete registry/dockerhub trigger-event codefresh delete trigger-event --context dockerhub registry:dockerhub:codefresh:fortune:push

Description Restart a build by its id.
Command codefresh restart &lt;id&gt;
Arguments    Option Alias Default Description     id   Build id    Options    Option Alias Default Description     - -help   Print help information   - -detach -d  Run build and print workflow ID    Examples Restart build ID and attach the created new build codefresh restart ID

